Comment: fluffyfitchick said "What's your blood type? For the last two years I couldn't donate blood because I didn't meet the 110lbs and above rule but since I have gained some fluff & üí™(muscles)  I can now happily donate. 
As an O Positive donor I am incredibly important to maintaining the blood supply in our community.  O Positive is the most common blood type and therefore needed by so many patients.

Here are some additional 
Facts about blood needs ‚Ä¢Every two seconds someone in the U.S. needs blood.
‚Ä¢More than 41,000 blood donations are needed every day.
‚Ä¢The blood type most often requested by hospitals is Type O.
‚Ä¢The blood used in an emergency is already on the shelves before the event occurs.
‚Ä¢More than 1.6 million people were diagnosed with cancer last year. Many of them will need blood, sometimes daily, during their chemotherapy treatment.
‚Ä¢A single car accident victim can require as many as 100 pints of blood.
‚Ä¢Although an estimated 38% of the U.S. population is eligible to donate, less than 10% actually do each year.
‚Ä¢Blood cannot be manufactured ‚Äì it can only come from generous donors.
‚Ä¢Donating blood is a safe process. A sterile needle is used only once for each donor and then discarded.
‚Ä¢Blood donation is a simple four-step process: registration, medical history and mini-physical, donation and refreshments. Process takes 10-12minutes.
‚Ä¢Two most common reasons cited by people who don't give blood are: "Never thought about it" and "I don't like needles."
‚Ä¢One donation can help save the lives of up to three people.
‚Ä¢If you began donating blood at age 17 and donated every 56 days until you reached 76, you would have donated 48 gallons of blood, potentially helping save more than 1,000 lives!
‚Ä¢Forty-five percent of people in the U.S. have Type O (positive or negative) blood. - facts taken from American Red Cross website #happy #healthy #give #donate #blood #weightloss #fitness #fitfam #fitnessfood #workout #gym #diet #cleaneating #eatclean #proactive #communitymember #savealife"
